<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Shell claviform, adult length 
<quantity box="[620,731,151,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="25.5" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="6.0">6â€“45 mm</quantity>
, often thick, base truncate, not strongly slanted to right, with short, wide, shallowly notched siphonal canal. Inner lip with a heavy parietal pad, constricting opening to the shallow to deep, U-shaped anal sinus, but not rendering it spout-like; outer lip with a distinct stromboid notch. Sculpture of axial ribs or peripheral nodules, spiral sculpture only on base of last whorl or absent. Protoconch domed to papilliform, of approximately two (rarely three) smooth whorls. Operculum oblanceolate, with terminal nucleus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Radula drilliine, central plate small, unicuspidate (sometimes with tiny side-cusps), laterals arched, pectinate, marginals somewhat awl-shaped, with weak blade and accessory limb.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,439,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Note.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[271,376,439,464]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Tylotiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[271,376,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Tylotiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been given full subgeneric or generic status by most authors (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Powell" box="[1190,1335,439,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Powell, A. W. B. (1966) The molluscan families Speightiidae and Turridae an evaluation of the valid taxa, both Recent and fossil, with lists of characteristic species. Bulletin of the Auckland Institute and Museum, 5, 1 - 184." type="journal article" year="1966">
Powell 
<number box="[1276,1335,439,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1966.0">1966</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kilburn" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Kilburn, R. N. (1988) Turridae (Mollusca: Gastropoda) of southern Africa and Mozambique. Part 4. Subfamilies Drilliinae, Crassispirinae and Strictispirinae. Annals of the Natal Museum, 29, 167 - 320." type="journal article" year="1988">
Kilburn 
<number box="[151,210,476,500]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poppe" box="[223,361,476,500]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refString="Poppe, G. (2008) Philippine Marine Molluscs. Vol. 2. Conchbooks, Hackenheim, Germany, 849 pp." type="book" year="2008">
Poppe 
<number box="[301,361,476,500]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), to include narrower species with a higher spire than in 
<emphasis box="[1011,1132,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName box="[1011,1089,476,501]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Clavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Clavus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1097,1132,477,500]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and axial ribs that extend over whole whorl height, and form neither spines nor angles. However, intermediate character states blur the dividing line, and we now prefer to regard 
<taxonomicName box="[630,736,548,573]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Tylotiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[630,736,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Tylotiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[932,1010,548,573]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Clavus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[932,1010,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Clavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
